.
.
Time stretched endlessly before us
I was afraid we wouldn't be able to fill it
our drama unfolded on completely different planes
pride, vanity... stupid preoccupations.
The kiss fell jerkily into the returned earth
for reasons of non-functionality
with love.
Our hands were tangled in detail
the yellow of the dandelions had covered our ankles
I had always preferred white hyacinths
we were eternal
and so bad!
.
