The mark of infinity,
Her needle's trajectory;
As she weaves not
Just her Mistress' fabric
But her fate and fortune.

The needle's grating rest
Against the cold thimble,
Had sewn many a gowns!
As, at night, her Ladyship
Dallies, and at funeral, mourns.

The cherry red and green on
Her puckered pincushion,
Had seen many a winter;
As she sailed through, gracefully,
Her Grace's playful banter.

An autumn and many more
Had she seen,
Alone in her dark dank room.
As her Mistress waded through
The advances of many a groom!

On, it goes, and for some more
The rhythm of the weaving hands
As the cosmos turns around
So does she, in waking nights
Until her eyes sleep sound.

